hadithEnglish:
Abd Allah bin Amr said &ldquo;A man came to the Prophet(ﷺ) and said &ldquo;Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ), May I take part in jihad?&rdquo; He asked &ldquo;Do you have parents?&rdquo; He replied &ldquo;Yes&rdquo;. So, strive for them.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said:
The name of the narrator Abu al-Abbas, a poet, is al-Saib b. Farrukh.

Al Sab bin Jaththamah said that he asked the Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) about the polytheists whose settlemnst were attacked at night when some of their offspring and women were smitten. The Prophet(ﷺ) &ldquo;They are of them. Amr bin Dinar used to say &ldquo;they are regarded in the same way as their parents.&rdquo;

Al-Zuhri said:
Thereafter the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) prohibited to kill women and children.

Abu Talhah said &ldquo;When the Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) prevailed on any people, he stayed three nights in the field. Ibn Al Muthanna said &ldquo;When he prevailed over people, he liked to stay three nights in the field.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;Yahya bin Said used to object to this tradition for this is not from his early traditions because his memory was spoiled at the age of forty five. He narrated this tradition in the last days of his age.&rdquo;

Abu Dawud said &ldquo; It is said that Waki  recived this tradition from him when his memory was spoiled.&rdquo;

Anas reported the Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ) as saying &ldquo;He who kills and infidel gets his spoil.&rdquo; Abu Talhah killed twenty men that day meaning the day of Hunain and got their spoils. Abu Talhah met Umm Sulaim who had a dagger with her. He asked &ldquo;What is with you, Umm Sulaim&rdquo;? She replied &ldquo;I swear by Allaah, I intended that if anyone came near me I would pierce his belly with it. Abu Talhah informed the Apostle of Allaah(ﷺ)about it.

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;This is good (hasan) tradition.

Abu Dawud said &ldquo;By this was meant dagger. The weapon used by the Non &ndash; Arabs in those days was dagger.&rdquo;
